examples.en: The launch was postponed to a later date.
The match had to be postponed until next week.
There is no question of the project being postponed.
The project has been postponed indefinitely.
He suggested that the case should be postponed.
The game was postponed due to inclement weather.
The concert has had to be postponed to next week.
The race was postponed in the interests of safety.
The ministry affirmed that the visit had been postponed.
The tour was postponed when the lead singer lost his voice.
She recommended to us that our trip be / should be postponed.
The baseball game was postponed until tomorrow because of rain.
The lawsuit will be postponed until the president leaves office.
